Viburnum lentago, commonly known as nannyberry, is a species of shrub or small tree.
It is a member of the family Adoxaceae and is native to North America.
The leaves are simple, dark green, and glossy with a finely serrated edge.
The flowers are creamy white and grow in clusters that can be up to 4 inches wide.
The berry-like fruits are dark blue-black and hang in clusters from the branches.
The bark of the Viburnum lentago is gray-brown and develops fissures as it ages.
It is commonly found in wooded areas, along streambanks, and in wetlands.
